        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Duplicate letter advantage:</span> KAYAK uses 2 K tiles, LEVEL uses 2 L tiles. If you draw duplicate letters, palindromes are one of the few word categories that actively use them.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">CIVIC and KAYAK score well:</span> Both contain high-value tiles (C=3, K=5, Y=4). They outperform many common 5-letter words and do not require rare tiles from the bag.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
